        "client_msg_id": "c9accc3a-6000-408a-95dd-025c585fc063",
        "text": "yeah makes perfect sense, also why I jumped at ATProto once I understood it. Its storage system mediator that retains data control to the data owner. So you get networked services but without lock-in. Big drawback is everything is public, they have an encryption workaround in the works (spaces), but apps can collaberate better if everything is public anyway so I don't even see that as a negative.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
